The way to the sea is about 300 meters long and must be done with clothing, but the Lido di Dante is a nudist beach for about a kilometer. The beach itself is said to be one of the 11 most beautiful in Italy, but it seems crowded and not really clean. But: the entry into the water is child-friendly and the sea is very warm! Back to the campsite: the places for caravans and tents are mostly shady and provide electricity, the mobile homes probably date from the 1990s. They are clean and technically okay. The prices are self-confident, but if you absolutely want to do nudist camping on the Adriatic or want to get to know the culture on an Italian campground (very familiar with each other and party-friendly), this is the place for you. What is annoying: the place must be vacated by 9 a.m. on the day of departure and it was very loud in the late evening.

title: Camping Libertin Le Ran du Chabrier
description: A paradise for hedonistic naturists. On the banks of the river Ceze in France. This  campsite leaves enough space to enjoy all the freedom and to live out the lust  regardless of whether you came alone or as couple. Everything you need for this is there: beautiful nature next to other open-minded people and enough possibilities to sunbathe and swim. There is also a small supermarket, a bar with a restaurant and a boutique for sexy lingerie. You find space for campers on one side and for tents on the other. If you like, you can also rent a cottage. The atmosphere is informal and friendly, many people seem to be regulars here. What is missing: more people under 50 ;) and free wifi in the whole area (there is no cell phone connection).

title: Camping Naturista Sierra Natura
description: An amazing campsite between Valencia and Murcia in inland Spain. The perfect oasis for families: with a great, large pool with waterfall and slide - a nice bar and a restaurant with the possibility of breakfast, lunch and dinner. The architecture looks extraordinary, inspired by Dali and Hundertwasser. The atmosphere is very friendly, very familiar. There are plenty of shady parking spaces and cool cottages to rent. All sanitary facilities are clean and functional. Next to the pool there is a trampoline, table tennis, boules and a small playground. The fact that there are also a small shop and various hiking or running routes complete the excellent picture of this campsite. For the off-season there is a sauna and whirlpool. Free wifi is available in the common room and the place has LTE connection. This makes Sierra Natura one of our favorite places!

title: Limmatspitz

title: Praia Naturista do Malhao
description: Wonderful, lonely nudist beach away from the two heavily frequented normal beaches. Accessible on foot or via a dirt road that starts at the end of the second parking lot. 4x4 recommended. The beach has wonderful dunes and a freshwater spring where you can take a shower. There are trash cans.

title: Monte Naturista O Barao
description: A real paradise for naturists, where the owners of the campsite, Laura and Jeff, personally welcome each guest to their property. The place offers plenty of space and there are large pitches in the sun or in the shade, plus cozy wooden houses for rent. Because Monte Naturista o Barao has 300 days of sunshine a year, you can also spend the winter here very well. There is a large pool, sauna and the option to buy snacks and drinks. Laura cooks once a week in the small canteen. Because the place is very quiet and close to nature, you can relax wonderfully here. It is also a good starting point for exploring the area: numerous sights and two well-known naturist beaches are easily accessible by car, and the area is ideal for hiking or jogging. That makes Monte Naturista o Barao an insider tip! What could still be improved: The Internet connection and the equipment for children. A trampoline and one or two pieces of play equipment would be great.

title: Camping Almanat Naturista-FKK
description: A naturist campsite under palm trees in the south of Spain, just a few meters from the Mediterranean Sea, with everything your heart desires? Sounds almost too good to be true, but there is: Camping-Naturista Almanat near the small town of Torre del Mar. The campsite offers many different sized pitches - some even, and this is new, with its own toilet including washing facilities. If you like, you can also rent a small bungalow with a roof terrace. Everything looks new and is very tidy, and the sanitary facilities on the site are super clean. There is a restaurant on the beach, a supermarket, a playground, sports equipment and a boules field. You find also a pool if it's too stormy by the sea. A lot of the  guests came from Spain and were mostly friendly. Our conclusion: If you want to experience naturism in the Mediterranean and are looking for a manageable, well-kept campsite with good facilities, this is the right place. But little things could still be improved: The opening times of the pool and supermarket, for example. Why are both closed from 2:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m.? And why is there no ice cream in the supermarket? What also bothered: the strict rules at the pool. Everything that is fun is forbidden, not even lying on an air mattress is allowed. And there is only paid WiFi. But thats about it.

title: NaturViana
description: The Garden of Eden in 2021: It could look like this! Here, where exotic plants bloom and natural springs gush, the two owners Nina and Adriano created a little paradise: with self-made yurts and a sensational glass bubble to stay overnight, with a vegetable garden and an ecological pool, a sweat house and a nice bar. Living in harmony with nature, that's why the electricity is generated by solar energy, the water comes from a spring and you have to use ecological toilets. The aim is to share as many wonderful experiences as possible with the guests. There is enough space for campers and tents, but NaturViana never receives more than 20 guests. In return, Nina and Adriano look after everyone wonderfully, they cook delicious dinners, offer yoga and massage, and you can book an off-road tour with an iconic, Portuguese UMM off-road vehicle.

It is positive that there are many offers for children and young people: a pool with a baby pool and power slide, a bouncy castle, trampoline, playground and basketball court. The square also offers children's entertainment and a program every evening: from karaoke to bands for young and old. In addition, there is a bar, a restaurant and a supermarket. Negative: there is no smartphone connectivity in the valley and the wifi is very expensive. In addition: the place looks rather old and the sanitary facilities are not particularly well-kept. The high prices don't match that at all.
